{% doc %}
  Renders a single product card per the Domaine Figma spec.

  Used by:
    - sections/featured-products.liquid

  Depends on:
    - snippets/responsive-image.liquid (responsive <img> rendering)
    - frontend/entrypoints/main.js (swatch click → image swap behavior)
    - locales/en.default.json (product_card.* user-facing strings)

  Implementation notes
  ────────────────────
    Hover swap (primary → secondary image) is pure CSS via Tailwind
    `group-hover:opacity-*`. Wrapped in `motion-safe:` so users with
    `prefers-reduced-motion` don't get the fade animation.

    Swatch click swap is JS-driven; the script reads `data-*` attributes
    on each swatch button (see frontend/entrypoints/main.js). On hover
    (pointerenter / focusin), the JS warms the browser cache for that
    variant's primary image so the click feels instant.

    Two anchors per card (image link + text link) navigate to the same
    URL. The image link is `aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"` so it is
    invisible to screen readers and skipped by keyboard tab — only the
    text link announces, but mouse/touch users can still click anywhere.

    Swatches are plain buttons (not a listbox) using `aria-pressed` to
    indicate selection. Listbox role would imply arrow-key navigation
    we don't implement. Each swatch has an invisible expanded hit area
    (`before:` pseudo) for comfortable touch targets on mobile.

    Variant → image lookup uses alt-text matching (Dawn convention):
      - Primary alt   = variant value, e.g. "Blue"
      - Secondary alt = variant value + " Secondary", e.g. "Blue Secondary"
      - Match is case-insensitive (downcase on both sides).
    Filenames change when re-uploaded; alt text is admin-controlled and
    survives re-uploads. The lookup is done inline (Shopify's `render`
    tag is variable-isolated — a helper snippet cannot return values to
    the parent scope, so we inline the 6 lines twice rather than fight
    that constraint).

    Spec colors (#0A4874 title, #FF0000 sale, #E8E8E8 border, #111111
    vendor) are inline Tailwind arbitrary values — they are not theme
    tokens because the Figma spec fixes them.

    Card border + radius are driven by parent CSS custom properties
    (--card-border-color, --card-radius) so the section's "Card style
    overrides" schema can tune them per instance, with sensible defaults.

    Swatch background uses the variant value as a CSS color name
    (e.g. "blue", "navy"). Works for the Domaine demo palette
    (Blue/Green/Navy/Orange/Pink/Yellow). Map to hex codes if the
    merchant ships colors with non-CSS names.

    Single-option (Color) products only — multi-option swatch mapping
    is out of scope for the assessment.

  Alternative variant→image strategies (kept here for future maintainers):

    1. Filename matching (image.src contains 'blue.', 'blue-secondary')
       Pro: zero admin setup. Con: breaks silently on re-upload rename.

    2. variant.featured_image + position (next image in product.images)
       Pro: Shopify-native. Con: requires strict admin image ordering.

    3. Variant metafield `custom.secondary_image` (file_reference)
       Pro: most robust. Con: per-variant admin setup.

  @param {product} product - Product object to render
  @param {boolean} [show_vendor] - Show product vendor (default true)
  @param {boolean} [show_swatches] - Show variant swatches (default true)
  @param {boolean} [show_sale_badge] - Show sale badge when on sale (default true)
  @param {boolean} [show_sold_out_badge] - Show sold-out badge when current variant is unavailable (default true)
  @param {string} [image_ratio] - 'square' | 'portrait' | 'natural' (default 'square')
  @param {string} [sale_badge_text] - Override locale string for the sale badge
  @param {string} [sold_out_badge_text] - Override locale string for the sold-out badge
  @param {string} [class] - Additional CSS classes on the article wrapper

  @example
  {% render 'product-card', product: product %}
  {% render 'product-card', product: product, image_ratio: 'portrait', show_vendor: false %}
{% enddoc %}

{% liquid
  assign show_vendor = show_vendor | default: true, allow_false: true
  assign show_swatches = show_swatches | default: true, allow_false: true
  assign show_sale_badge = show_sale_badge | default: true, allow_false: true
  assign show_sold_out_badge = show_sold_out_badge | default: true, allow_false: true
  assign image_ratio = image_ratio | default: 'square'

  assign current_variant = product.selected_or_first_available_variant
  assign on_sale = false
  if current_variant.compare_at_price > current_variant.price
    assign on_sale = true
  endif
  assign is_sold_out = false
  unless current_variant.available
    assign is_sold_out = true
  endunless

  assign sale_text = sale_badge_text
  if sale_text == blank
    assign sale_text = 'product_card.sale_badge' | t
  endif
  assign sold_out_text = sold_out_badge_text
  if sold_out_text == blank
    assign sold_out_text = 'product_card.sold_out_badge' | t
  endif

  case image_ratio
    when 'portrait'
      assign aspect_class = 'aspect-[3/4]'
    when 'natural'
      assign aspect_class = 'aspect-auto'
    else
      assign aspect_class = 'aspect-square'
  endcase

  # ── Variant → image lookup for the initial (current) variant ──
  assign variant_key = current_variant.title | downcase
  assign primary_image = blank
  assign secondary_image = blank
  for image in product.images
    assign image_alt = image.alt | default: '' | downcase
    if image_alt contains variant_key
      if image_alt contains 'secondary'
        assign secondary_image = image
      else
        assign primary_image = image
      endif
    endif
  endfor
  assign primary_image = primary_image | default: current_variant.featured_image | default: product.featured_image
  assign secondary_image = secondary_image | default: primary_image
%}

<article
  class="flex flex-col {{ class }}"
  data-product-card
  data-product-id="{{ product.id }}"
>
  <a
    href="{{ product.url }}"
    tabindex="-1"
    aria-hidden="true"
    class="group relative block {{ aspect_class }} overflow-hidden bg-white border rounded-[var(--card-radius,10px)] border-[color:var(--card-border-color,#E8E8E8)]"
  >
    {%- if primary_image -%}
      {%- render 'responsive-image'
        , image: primary_image
        , class: 'absolute inset-0 w-full h-full object-cover motion-safe:transition-opacity motion-safe:duration-300 group-hover:opacity-0'
        , sizes: '(min-width: 1024px) 33vw, (min-width: 640px) 50vw, 100vw'
        , data_role: 'primary'
      -%}
    {%- endif -%}

    {%- if secondary_image -%}
      {%- render 'responsive-image'
        , image: secondary_image
        , class: 'absolute inset-0 w-full h-full object-cover opacity-0 motion-safe:transition-opacity motion-safe:duration-300 group-hover:opacity-100'
        , sizes: '(min-width: 1024px) 33vw, (min-width: 640px) 50vw, 100vw'
        , alt: ''
        , aria_hidden: true
        , data_role: 'secondary'
      -%}
    {%- endif -%}

    {%- if show_sale_badge or show_sold_out_badge -%}
      <div class="absolute top-4 left-4 flex flex-col items-start gap-2">
        {%- if show_sold_out_badge -%}
          <span
            data-role="sold-out-badge"
            class="px-4 py-1 bg-[color:var(--badge-bg,#FFFFFF)] border border-[#111111] rounded-full text-[#111111] text-sm font-medium {% unless is_sold_out %}hidden{% endunless %}"
          >
            {{ sold_out_text }}
          </span>
        {%- endif -%}

        {%- if show_sale_badge -%}
          <span
            data-role="sale-badge"
            class="px-4 py-1 bg-[color:var(--badge-bg,#FFFFFF)] border border-[#FF0000] rounded-full text-[#FF0000] text-sm font-medium {% if is_sold_out or on_sale == false %}hidden{% endif %}"
          >
            {{ sale_text }}
          </span>
        {%- endif -%}
      </div>
    {%- endif -%}
  </a>

  <div class="flex flex-col gap-3 pt-4">
    {%- if show_swatches and product.variants.size > 1 -%}
      <ul
        class="flex flex-wrap gap-3"
        aria-label="{{ 'product_card.swatches_label' | t }}"
      >
        {%- for variant in product.variants -%}
          {%- liquid
            # Per-variant inline lookup (same logic as above; see header
            # note on render-scope isolation).
            assign v_key = variant.title | downcase
            assign v_primary = blank
            assign v_secondary = blank
            for image in product.images
              assign image_alt = image.alt | default: '' | downcase
              if image_alt contains v_key
                if image_alt contains 'secondary'
                  assign v_secondary = image
                else
                  assign v_primary = image
                endif
              endif
            endfor
            assign v_primary = v_primary | default: variant.featured_image | default: product.featured_image
            assign v_secondary = v_secondary | default: v_primary

            assign swatch_color = variant.title | downcase
            assign variant_on_sale = false
            if variant.compare_at_price > variant.price
              assign variant_on_sale = true
            endif
          -%}
          <li>
            <button
              type="button"
              data-swatch
              data-variant-id="{{ variant.id }}"
              data-primary="{{ v_primary | image_url: width: 800 }}"
              data-primary-srcset="{{ v_primary | image_url: width: 400 }} 400w, {{ v_primary | image_url: width: 800 }} 800w, {{ v_primary | image_url: width: 1200 }} 1200w"
              data-secondary="{{ v_secondary | image_url: width: 800 }}"
              data-secondary-srcset="{{ v_secondary | image_url: width: 400 }} 400w, {{ v_secondary | image_url: width: 800 }} 800w, {{ v_secondary | image_url: width: 1200 }} 1200w"
              data-price="{{ variant.price | money }}"
              data-compare-price="{{ variant.compare_at_price | money }}"
              data-on-sale="{{ variant_on_sale }}"
              data-available="{{ variant.available }}"
              aria-label="{{ variant.title | escape }}{% unless variant.available %} ({{ 'product_card.unavailable' | t }}){% endunless %}"
              aria-pressed="{% if variant.id == current_variant.id %}true{% else %}false{% endif %}"
              class="relative size-6 rounded-full overflow-hidden border border-black/10 ring-offset-2 ring-[var(--color-foreground,#333333)] cursor-pointer motion-safe:transition-shadow hover:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:outline-none aria-pressed:ring-2 before:absolute before:-inset-1 before:content-[''] before:rounded-full {% unless variant.available %}opacity-50{% endunless %}"
              style="background-color: {{ swatch_color }};"
            >
              {%- unless variant.available -%}
                <span class="pointer-events-none absolute inset-0 flex items-center justify-center" aria-hidden="true">
                  <span class="block w-[140%] h-[2px] bg-[#FF0000] rotate-45"></span>
                </span>
              {%- endunless -%}
            </button>
          </li>
        {%- endfor -%}
      </ul>
    {%- endif -%}

    <a href="{{ product.url }}" class="flex flex-col gap-1 no-underline">
      {%- if show_vendor and product.vendor != blank -%}
        <p class="text-[#111111] text-sm">{{ product.vendor }}</p>
      {%- endif -%}

      <h3 class="text-[#0A4874] text-lg font-medium leading-tight">
        {{ product.title }}
      </h3>

      <p class="flex items-baseline gap-2 mt-1" data-role="price-block">
        <span
          data-role="compare-price"
          class="text-[#111111] line-through {% unless on_sale %}hidden{% endunless %}"
        >
          {{ current_variant.compare_at_price | money }}
        </span>
        <span
          data-role="price"
          class="{% if on_sale %}text-[#FF0000]{% else %}text-[#111111]{% endif %}"
        >
          {{ current_variant.price | money }}
        </span>
      </p>
    </a>
  </div>
</article>
